<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Family-Fire     06-10 0099</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Family-Fire,0102</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Eight Die In Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire ripped through a two-story
house today, killing a shopkeeper's family of eight in Penang, an
island city on the west coast of Malaysia.
   Senior Fire Officer Ismail Zainuddin told the National News
Agency Bernama today that the fire apparently started from the back
portion of the top floor of the building while businessman Tan Twan
Guan, 53, and his family were fast asleep.
   Ismail estimated damage at $100,000.
   The cause of fire was not known.
   Penang is 180 miles northwest of the capital, Kuala Lumpur.
</TEXT>
