<HEAD>Marine Dies In Accidental Shooting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Marines were killed when an M-60
machine gun accidentally discharged while they were handing it
through a window at Camp Hanson in Okinawa, officials said.
   Pfc. Mark Joseph Henderson of Louisville and Lance Cpl. Peter L.
Orazio of Derry, Pa., died Monday, said Gunnery Sgt. Terry Nummer,
