<HEAD>Pianist to Make First Dallas Appearance in 10 Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pianist Van Cliburn is to perform in Dallas for
the first time in 11 years at the inauguration next year of the new
home of the Dallas Symphony Orchestra.
   The concert at the Morton S. Meyerson Symphony Center is
scheduled Sept. 8, 1989, a symphony official said Thursday.
   The pianist, who lives in Fort Worth, began to perform again
