<HEAD>One Man Killed, Another Wounded By Same Bullet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One man was killed and another seriously
wounded by the same bullet, police said.
   Police spokesman Roger Austin said Peter Garcia, 18, was holding
the gun pointed at his head Thursday when it went off, apparently
accidentally. The bullet went through Garcia's head and struck Luke
Schinzel, 19, in the face, police said.
