<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--PoliceWagonEscape     06-10 0177</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Police Wagon Escape,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four Suspects Flee Through Police Wagon Floor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four drug suspects pried apart the wooden
floorboards of a police wagon and escaped, triggering a review of
the aging vehicles, police said Friday.
   ``I suppose it's embarrassing,'' Lt. Gary Hall said of
Thursday's escape from a wagon estimated to be at least 20 years
old.
   Two of the four men were quickly captured, but the two were
still free Friday, Hall said.
   ``Over the years the floorboard had cracked and deteriorated,''
Hall said. ``Somehow the suspects managed to loop a shoestring
around the cracked board, pried it up, broke it and pulled up some
other boards.''
   The men slithered through the 24-by-30-inch hole and fled, he
said.
   The four men had been arrested for investigation of narcotics
sales. They were locked in the wagon at the Hollywood station for
transfer to police headquarters.
   ``Most of the paddy wagons have steel floors,'' Hall said.
``They'll have to put some sheet metal in this one and I guess
check them all citywide.''
</TEXT>
