<HEAD>Gunmen Shoot Wounded Hospital Patient</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OCALA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two gunmen burst into a hospital room Friday
and critically wounded a patient who had been shot in a barroom
brawl 24 hours earlier, authorities said.
   The gunmen fired another shot in the hall of the Monroe Regional
Medical Center as they fled, but no one else was hurt, said police
Sgt. Ken Hall.
   ``We are leaning toward some kind of bad blood grudge between
the victim and one of the suspects now at large,'' said Hall. ``We
have tentative identifications on the two suspects and are trying
to run them down.''
   The victim, Juan Ward, 27, was in critical condition Friday. He
was shot in the chest during a fight Thursday at Gwen's Inn. Two
other men were injured, and one was also admitted, but he was in
another part of the hospital when Ward was shot.
   Hall said the gunmen first entered a room next to Ward's and
threatened a patient by showing him a weapon and ordering him to
remain silent. They moved into Ward's room about 10 minutes later
and fired twice, hitting Ward in the chest and abdomen.
