<HEAD>5 Cubans Riding Inner Tubes Picked Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five Cubans riding inner tubes tied together for
nearly five days were picked up Friday by a pleasure boat between
the island of Bimini and Miami, the Coast Guard said.
   The Immigration and Naturalization Service took custody of the
Cubans, who requested political asylum. The five, ages 15 to 42,
all said they have relatives in Miami.
   ``They were in fairly good health considering they had been at
sea for almost a week,'' said Petty Officer Tom Gillespie, Coast
Guard spokesman. ``They were talking and walking around.''
   The men carried knapsacks with a few possessions, Gillespie
said. They said they departed Sunday night from Matanzas, about 50
miles east of Havana.
