<2ND_LINE>AM-Cricket-Sex,0348</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cricket Captain Replaced Over Woman In Hotel Room</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A new captain was picked for England's
international cricket team on Friday after his predecessor was
ousted for inviting a woman to his hotel room.
   John Emburey, 35, took over the prestigious post from
31-year-old Michael Gatting, who was dismissed Thursday following a
series of sex scandal stories in Britain's tabloid press. Gatting
will remain as batsman on the team.
   Gatting, who is married and the father of two children, denied
allegations in the tabloids that he had taken a woman to his hotel
room for sex last weekend during a five-day game against the West
Indies in England. He said he was suing the newspapers for libel.
   The game's governing body, the Test and County Cricket Board,
announced it believed Gatting's assertion that there was no
``sexual impropriety'' but said he acknowledged inviting the woman
to his room for a drink. In doing this, the board said, Gatting
``behaved irresponsibly''
   Cricket has been played in England for more than 700 years and
an insistence on impeccable behavior on and off the playing field
is a deeply imbedded tradition.
   In addition to the allegations about the captain, the
mass-circulation Sun said two other players had sex with two women
on the lawn outside their hotel at the same game.
   Four players from the team were summoned Friday to Lord's
cricket ground, the Mecca of the sport in London, to take part in
the cricket board's inquiry into the matter.
   After the meeting, the board said the four players had not been
accused of any offense, and their behavior was ``above reproach.''
   Because of the scandal, Gatting stepped down from the team for
the next match, starting June 16, but he is not barred from later
participation.
   Team manager Mickey Stewart defended the decision to fire
Gatting, saying he had ``paid the penalty'' for making himself
vulnerable to the tabloid press.
   Gatting has played for England 59 times and has captained the
team since June 1986.
</TEXT>
