<FILEID>AP-NR-06-10-88 0803EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     06-10 0106</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0113</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares Lower At Midday; FT-SE 100 Off 1.7</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices drifted aimlessly lower in London at
midday Friday in typically sluggish pre-weekend trading.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index fell 1.7
points, or 0.09 percent, to 1,839.8.
   Dealers said the market appeared to be pausing near the
1,840-level after chalking up some gains earlier in the week.
   Several market players were disappointed by declines on Wall
Street and Tokyo. Overall, however, little was happening.
   ``It's a typical quiet Friday and there's nothing I could tell
you about this market that I wouldn't be making up,'' said one
equity dealer.
</TEXT>
