<HEAD>PNC Chairman Moving to Meritor Financial</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Roger S. Hillas says he will retire June 24 as
chairman of PNC Financial Corp. to become chairman of Meritor
Financial Group, the Philadelphia-based thrift.
   There was no immediate announcement on his successor.
   Hillas said Thursday he will recommend his positions as chairman
and chief executive officer of PNC's Philadelphia-based Provident
National Group go to Robert E. Chappell, who is now Provident's
president.
   Hillas, 61, has been chief executive officer of the Provident
companies since 1973. He has been president then chairman of PNC
since the company was formed in the 1983 combination of Provident
National and Pittsburgh National Corp. Hillas joined Provident in
1951.
   Hillas will be faced with conducting the struggling Meritor
through a restructuring that began last fall. The thrift has had
only two profitable quarters over the past three years.
