<HEAD>Auto Production Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
261,618 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
210,774, Ward's Automotive Reports said Friday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 221,507 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 174,711 cars this week,
compared with 138,745 a week ago and 147,277 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 86,907,
compared with last week's 72,029 and last year's 74,230.
   Canadian automakers were to build 27,117 cars this week, up from
26,559 a week ago and up from last year's 18,115.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 20,440,
compared with 20,202 a week ago and 18,563 in the same week last
year.
