<HEAD>Lucky To Sell 38 Stores In Arizona</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lucky Stores Inc. said Friday it has
entered into an agreement to sell its 38 supermarkets in Arizona to
Phoenix-based ABCO Markets.
   The sale will increase the ABCO chain to 75 stores, making it
one of the three largest supermarket chains in Arizona. The terms
of the sale were not disclosed.
   ``We are pleased with the opportunity to build upon the
strengths of both companies,'' said Ed Hill, president of ABCO.
   The company is controlled by Odyssey Partners, a New York
private investment group.
   Lucky agreed about three weeks ago to be acquired for $2.5
billion in cash by American Stores Co., of Salt Lake City, which
owns the Alpha Beta chain.
</TEXT>
