<1ST_LINE>r f AM-MineLayoff     06-10 0100</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Mine Layoff,0104</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Duquesne Light Closes Mine; 225 Laid Off</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Duquesne Light Co. said Friday it will close
its Warwick Mine in Greene County, Pa., and will lay off about 225
miners.
   The utility said the underground mine, on the Monongahela River
about 83 miles upstream from Pittsburgh, will close at 12:01 a.m.
Monday. It said a small number of miners will maintain the mine
while it is closed.
   Duquesne Light said it has excess coal reserves ``due to the
last two months of light system loads'' and ``despite recent
declines in productivity at the mine.''
</TEXT>
