<2ND_LINE>AM-Isuzu Recall,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Isuzu Recalling Trooper II for Brake Defect</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WHITTIER, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Isuzu Motors Inc. is
voluntarily recalling all 22,591 of its 1988 Trooper II cars to
correct a brake defect, a company official said Friday.
   The company isn't aware of any accidents or injuries resulting
from the problem, which causes a loss of braking power in the rear
wheels, spokeswoman Susan Cain said.
   Owners of the Jeep-like vehicles are being notified by mail and
can take the cars to a dealer for repairs, the company said.
   The defect is in a component of the rear disk brakes, which has
come loose during shipping in some cases, causing a partial loss of
braking power.
</TEXT>
